The paper deals with the problem of geo-locating an image using image matching in a structured database of city-wide reference images with known GPS coordinates. This problem is primarily related to computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves matching local image features and clustering them to obtain a global solution. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques such as Dominant Set clustering, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with large-scale datasets of street view images, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
